==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glockenspiel
<hw>Glock"en*spiel`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.;
<ets>glocke</ets> bell + <ets>spiel</ets> play.]</ety>
<fld>(Music)</fld> <def>An instrument, originally a series of bells on
an iron rod, now a set of flat metal bars, diatonically tuned, giving a
bell-like tone when played with a mallet; a carillon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glode</ent>⟦br⟧
